{
  "texts": [
    "Unexpectedly, PEU exerted an insignificant effect on BI (β = 0.011, p value > 0.05), indicating that PEU plays an unimportant role in predicting students' BI toward the adoption of the metaverse.",
    "However, PEU influenced both PU (β = 0.128, p value < 0.01) and PE (β = 0.604, p value < 0.001) positively and significantly, implying that PEU has an important role in boosting PU and PE.",
    "As proposed, PCR serves as a key obstacle of students' BI with regard to metaverse adoption and with regard to PU, as it displayed significant negative effects on BI (β = -0.158, p value < 0.05) and PU (β = -0.315, p value < 0.01).",
    "With respect to predictive power (R 2) (Table 6), the effects of PIIT, PEU, PU, PE, and PCR on BI yielded an R 2 of 0.753, denoting that these factors explained a total of 75.3% of the variance in BI.",
    "Such an explanatory power is recognized substantial (Henseler et al., 2009)."
  ]
}